1. create mounts from image for boot and root
1.a. Download image
1.b. extract image
1.c. mount boot from image
1.d. mount root from image
--> 1_init-ubuntu-image.yaml

2. prepare /tftpboot
2.a. copy boot from ubuntuboot to /tftpboot/<serial>
2.b. change cmdline.txt in /tftpboot/<serial> to ??
TOBE DONE for every node!
--> 2_init-boot-from-ubuntu-image.yaml

3. create partitions on USB-Drive
3.a. wipe all partitions
3.b. create n primary partitions
3.c. create ext4 filesystem on partitions
3.d. label partitions
3.e. mount tgtroot (to store ubuntu root in 4)
--> 3_init-us-drive.yaml
TOBE DONE for every node!

4. prepare root on USB
--> 4_init-root-from-ubuntu-image.yaml
TOBE DONE for every node!
